ABSTRACT
Communication network architectures, systems, and meth-
ods for supporting a network of mobile nodes are disclosed.
As a non-limiting example, various aspects of this disclosure
provide communication network architectures, systems, and
methods for supporting a dynamically configurable commu-
nication network comprising a complex array of both static
and moving communication nodes (e.g., the Internet of
moving things), where the network may involve autono-
mous and/or non-autonomous vehicles.
